author_ssm: Camilla Fojas, 1997. Finding aid updated by Laura Newsome, 2010. Accretions added by Lawrence Giffin, 2011.
abstract_ssm: Richard Kostelanetz is a major figure in the New York City downtown literary and art scene, as well as a performer, critic, scholar and an authority on concrete poetry. Included in the collection are copies of his printed works, including essays, anthologies, assemblings, contributions to periodicals, etc. Included also are: videos, sound recordings, and other materials which Kostelanetz produced from 1961-1997.
